Now that instances are not protected by default (and have names that let them stay unprotected), I think we should move towards unqualifying the names
```suggestion
  { semiring, instSemilatticeSup, instOrderBot with
```

I'd rather leave that to a follow-up; it's much easier to do a replacement of  `Foo.instBar` with `instBar` via a regex later.

It's also not fully clear to me whether unprotected instances is the right choice.
That's technically scope-creep wrt your PR description, but I'm fine with it
Good catch, after changing this one I realized I was taking on too much at once.
